HEADWORD: Cypsela
<hw>Cyp"se*la</hw> <pr>(s?p"s?-l?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>kypse`lh</grk> any hollow vessel.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A one-seeded, one-celled, indehiscent fruit; an achene with the
calyx tube adherent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

